legacy.full_text: The Chinese Foreign Ministry has described Lai Ching-te as a "troublemaker through and through." Lai, a staunch advocate of "Taiwan independence," has openly identified himself as a "pragmatic Taiwan independence worker."

legacy.description: Commentator, Host of CGTN Radio/China Radio International. zhaoyingcri@foxmail.com
legacy.name: Zhao Ying

legacy.full_text: Although Lai has recently rejected the “golden grandson of Taiwan independence” label, his “stopover” once again laid bare his stance.

legacy.description: Commentator, Host of CGTN Radio/China Radio International. zhaoyingcri@foxmail.com
legacy.name: Zhao Ying

legacy.full_text: Using the guise of a "stopover," Lai has actively pursued the strategy of "relying on the US for independence." This approach blatantly contravenes the One China principle and endangers the peace and stability of the Taiwan Straits.
